---

## Debrief after clearing wa30 L8

L8 is a TWO-socket world.  Two 9-frame/2-core socket containers (top-right,
bottom-right), each served by an auto-seating courier (colour 12) AND sabotaged
by a roaming self-mover STEALER (colour 15, one per horizontal band) that pulls
boxes back OUT of its socket -- so a courier can never finish while its stealer
roams (socket cores sit at a stable equilibrium under pure idle).

Key discovered mechanics (all from raw frames):
- Avatar = head colour 0 over body colour 14 (the existing `_grid_scan`/`_cells`
  readers already model it); bump-face + USE grabs a 4-border/9-core box which
  then rigid-carries; releasing it inside a socket permanently covers core.
- Budget: a per-level colour-7 bar gives ~150 steps, but the HARNESS also caps
  total real moves at ~600; the 466-move L1-7 replay leaves only ~134 for L8.
- A stealer moves at the avatar's own speed, so it CANNOT be tail-chased; a
  facing USE only removes it when we are adjacent AND our last move was toward
  it.  It bounces in a fixed loop, so navigating INTO its loop region and then
  pursuing corners it quickly (bottom stealer: approach (14,7) => 24 steps vs
  53 for a far approach).  Removal is permanent (no respawn).

Solution shape (new, general legs):
- `chase_and_clear(env, color, band_pred, approach)` -- enter a band, pursue a
  same-speed self-mover (box/wall-aware BFS + greedy fallback) and USE it away.
- `fill_dual_sockets(env, top_cells, bot_cells, split_row)` -- deliver the box
  nearest the avatar into an open cell of its band's socket, ceding turns to the
  couriers when nothing is grabbable; runs to level-up or budget.
- `clear_stealers_then_fill_dual(...)` -- the L8 composite: clear each band's
  stealer, then drain both sockets.  `play_level_8` is one data-driven call.

This is a sibling of the L6/L7 "neutralise the blocking agent, then deliver"
skeleton, generalised to TWO blockers + TWO goal containers, where the
neutralise verb is a same-speed pursuit-and-USE instead of thread-gap /
idle-until-frozen.  RESULT: `levels=8 moves=588 replay_ok=True`.
EOF
